A clean, modern website built as part of the DevOps Micro-Internship program.  
Focus: Hands-on DevOps practices (Git workflows, CI/CD concepts, cloud deployment to EC2) + Agile delivery using Scrum in Jira.

## 📖 Project Overview

This project demonstrates real-world DevOps and Agile skills by:
- Improving a basic website UI (header, buttons, hero, footer, CTA, contact section)
- Breaking work into Epics → Stories → Sub-tasks
- Estimating with Fibonacci story points
- Running sprints with clear goals
- Planning future deployment to AWS EC2

Built as a static site (HTML/CSS/JS) — ready for future enhancements like CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions), containerization, or IaC.

## ✨ Key Features Implemented (Sprint 1)

- Updated site header: “DevOps Micro-Internship — Learn by Building”
- Refreshed primary button color with better contrast
- Improved hero subtitle copy
- Added versioned footer with deployment date
- Added Contact/About section (placeholders)
- Added “Join the DMI Waitlist” CTA button

→ Total committed points in Sprint 1: 4 pts (header, subtitle, CTA focus)

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- HTML5
- CSS3 (custom styles + potential Bootstrap/Tailwind later)
- JavaScript (vanilla, for future interactivity)
- Deployment target: AWS EC2 (pending)
- Project management: Jira Cloud (Team-managed Scrum)

## 📋 Agile / Scrum Setup in Jira

**Project**: DevOps Micro-Internship Website – George (Key: DMIWEB)  
**Epic**: Polish DMI Website UI & Deploy  
**Backlog**: 6 user stories with Gherkin acceptance criteria, labels (frontend/devops), story points (1/2/3 Fibonacci)  
**Sub-tasks**: Detailed breakdown on key stories (edit → test → deploy → verify)  
**Sprint 1**: 1-week sprint, goal = “Ship visible DMI Website UI polish (header, color, footer/CTA) to EC2 with screenshots”  
**Reports**: Burndown chart enabled for tracking

Full Jira setup screenshots and details are available in the assignment Google Doc: [Link to your Google Doc]

